ce:section.ce:para:
The quenching of the fluorescence of Trp-CD by ONOO− was studied by Stern–Volmer plots and at two temperatures (Fig. 6
                        ). The analysis of these plots shows their linear trend with Stern–Volmer constants (K
                        SV) of 9900±800 (20°C) and 4460±190 (37°C)M−1. Taking into consideration the magnitude of these constants and its temperature dependence a static quenching is observed probably due to a chemical reaction between ONOO− and the tryptophan residues in the CD (nitration or oxidation reaction).
